2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The Subset Sum problem is a well-known problem in discrete mathematics, and the paper uses generating functions and FFT to solve its counting version modulo prime p>t. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the time complexity of the Subset Sum problem and presents a near-linear pseudopolynomial time algorithm. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses FFT to manipulate generating functions, which is a technique commonly used in information theory. 
5. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - Although not directly related to computational geometry, the Subset Sum problem has applications in computational geometry, such as in the design of efficient algorithms for packing and covering problems.
